body:
During testing with Docker on Ubuntu, `CloseEvaluatorTest` frequently consumes all CPUs and hangs. I reduce the number of evaluators to `4` to use the limit of local-runtime tests. I think it's enough. If we need a real stress test, we can make a separate suite (not in unit tests or in integration tests).

```
-  private static final int NUM_EVALUATORS = 16;
+  private static final int NUM_EVALUATORS = 4;
```

@afchung @markusweimer I am sorry I just saw this PR was merged. I feel the tests are still useful. Those tests were created to test alias and evaluator configurations. We don't have other tests to cover them. The tests are especially useful when Java side changed evaluator configuration settings, we can then replace the evaluator.config and repro the issue. I used it for debug many times. 
Another test covered by those are alias. Even alias is Tang annotation and we can use Tang unit test to do it. The purpose of those tests are to make sure all the alias are created and set correctly for the configurations we use in the evaluators. That cannot be covered by Tang unit testing. 
I agree for now the evaluator.config is copied offline in the test. What we need is to improve it to make it to automatic, for example, use the evaluator.config generated on the fly. Before we make the improvement, we should not just simply remove those tests.
